Stand-up comedian Klint da Drunk has said location must be given utmost consideration when planning a comedy show. The funnyman who earned his stage name in the course of acting like a drunkard in a chat with Hip TV argued location is a big factor to consider while preparing to host a comedy show.   Five Nigerian celebrities holding political offices     Ronaldo challenges 2Baba to be better dad     Singer T-Classic hospitalised after alleged poisoning   According to the comic star, if the location is overlooked or downplayed in the course of preparing for a comedy show, it has the ability to significantly impact the turnout of guests negatively. “Don’t use location as criteria. It’s only you and two people from your family that will come for the show,” he said.